{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsZ9X2sauWUBZy3Lh337","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All verification criteria are satisfied. Summary:\n\n**Detected & corrected:** The `es-cluster` StatefulSet had been externally scaled down to 1 replica. Scaled it back to 3 and confirmed all 3 original pods rejoined and were Ready before proceeding.\n\n**Deployed:**\n- `ConfigMap/es-config-new` — same TLS/security config as originals, but `node.roles: [data, ingest]` (data-only, non-master-eligible) and `node.attr.hardware: new`\n- `StatefulSet/es-data-new` (2 replicas, pods `es-data-new-0/1`) — uses a distinct selector (`tier: data-new`) to avoid controller overlap with `es-cluster`, while sharing the `app: elasticsearch` label so the existing headless `es-transport` service includes them for discovery\n\n**Verified:**\n1. Cluster health `green`, 5 nodes / 5 data nodes ✓\n2. Created index `app-data` (2 shards, 1 replica) with `index.routing.allocation.require.hardware: new` — all 4 shard copies landed exclusively on `es-data-new-0/1`, none on the original 3 nodes ✓\n3. `_cat/nodeattrs` shows `hardware=new` only on the two new nodes; originals have no such attribute ✓\n4. `es-cluster` StatefulSet remains at 3 replicas (3/3 ready); the new nodes live in a separate StatefulSet ✓\n\nAlso confirmed writes/reads succeed against `app-data` through the `es-http` service."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1099,"cache_read_input_tokens":117564,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1099},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2be9da49-6c7a-4500-bc30-0658ab36672e","uuid":"96078d3c-0a4e-430f-b94e-a07a2906d859","request_id":"req_011CcsZ9VGxUHBqXWgh7DrxV"}
